'''Martha J. Fleischman''' is an American [[art dealer]] and the former publisher of ''[[American Art (journal)|American Art]]''. She is the president of the Kennedy Galleries.<ref name="Kinsella">{{cite web|last1=Kinsella|first1=Eileen|title=Kennedy Galleries to Close, Will Go On as Private Entity|url=http://www.artnews.com/2005/02/01/kennedy-galleries-to-close-will-go-on-as-private-entity/|website=ArtNews|accessdate=30 April 2017}}</ref> Fleischman serves as a board member of [[New York Public Radio]] and [[Democracy Now!]]. She is a trustee of the [[Archives of American Art]]. She is the former board member of the Art Dealers Association.<ref name="SciFri">{{cite web|title=Martha J. Fleischman|url=https://www.sciencefriday.com/person/martha-j-fleischman/|website=Science Friday|accessdate=30 April 2017}}</ref> Her father was [[Lawrence A. Fleischman]].<ref name="Kinsella"/>

